cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with unsupervised learning of interest points in images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel training framework that involves optimization of properties, which is a machine learning approach (cs.LG). The use of latent variables and Expectation Maximization algorithm also suggests the paper could belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the experiments involve image matching benchmarks, which could also place the paper in the multimedia sub-category (cs.MM).
